  "body": "### Description\n\nCurrently, when a JsonRPC method throws an exception, the Dev UI receives a useless general message like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\"id\":6,\"error\":{\"code\":-32603,\"message\":\"Method [io.quarkiverse.langchain4j.quarkus-langchain4j-core.newConversation] failed: java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException\"},\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nand there is no way to pass any custom exception message. We should implement error handling per https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification#error_object and allow passing server errors\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
